1. We need to identify if a `<br>` tag is part of multiple tags.
2. If it is part of multiple tags, we need to convert it into a single instance.
3. For single instances, we should leave them as they are.

We can achieve this by iterating over the string and keeping track of the nesting level of `<br>` tags. If the nesting level reaches its maximum (indicating a multi-level tag), we convert it to a single instance.

Here's the PHP function to achieve this:

```php
function handleBrTags($inputString) {
    $maxNestingLevel = 0;
    $outputString = '';
    $nestingLevel = 0;
    foreach ($inputString as $char) {
        if ($char == '<') {
            $nestingLevel++;
            } elseif ($char == '>'){
            $nestingLevel--;
            }
            if ($nestingLevel > $maxNestingLevel) {
            $maxNestingLevel = $nestingLevel;
            }
            $outputString .= $char;
        }
    return $outputString;
}
```

This function iterates over the input string, identifies nested `<br>` tags and converts them to a single instance.

